The Academic Staff union of Universities (ASUU) has declared an indefinite strike. ASUU President Professor Biodun Ogunyem declared this yesterday while addressing journalists at the union’s National Secretariat in Abuja. The union had on March 9 embarked on a two-week warning strike over the Integrated Payroll and Personnel Information System, among others. Biodun said: “NEC resolved, to embark on a total, comprehensive and indefinite strike beginning Monday, 23 March 2020 until the issues are satisfactorily resolved.” He alleged that the federal government resorted to use  “hunger as a weapon of war” university lecturers. Breaking: ASUU declares indefinite strike FG, ASUU hold conciliation meeting Universities grounded as ASUU embarks on strike